**Overall meaning:**

"Even that sin which cannot be removed by hundreds of penances prescribed for pilgrimage sites like Prayag, even that sin will be destroyed quickly."

**Interpretation:**

This verse emphasizes the exceptional power of the mantra in comparison to traditional methods of atonement. It suggests that even sins deemed irredeemable through traditional practices, like pilgrimages and penances, can be effectively cleansed through chanting the mantra.  The verse underscores the transformative power of devotion and highlights the mantra as a superior path to spiritual purification. It emphasizes the possibility of achieving complete liberation from sin through unwavering dedication to the divine name. 
